const EMBEDDED_POWERS = [{"name":"Invincibility","path":"Brick Power/Invincibility.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                         |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Damage Resistance 1**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +3 armour  |\n| 2     | 1      | **Damage Resistance 2**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +6 armour  |\n| 3     | 1      | **Damage Resistance 3**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +9 armour  |\n| 4     | 2      | **Damage Resistance 4**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +12 armour |\n"},{"name":"Rage","path":"Brick Power/Rage.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                         |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Berserker**\u003cbr\u003e-You take and deal double damage for the next combat encounter |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Regeneration","path":"Brick Power/Regeneration.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                         |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Flesh Regrowth**\u003cbr\u003e-You regain 2 hp per round                |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Limb Regrowth**\u003cbr\u003e-You heal from critical damage once a week |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Super Strength","path":"Brick Power/Super Strength.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                         |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Enhanced Strength**\u003cbr\u003e-Gives you +2 strength |\n| 2     | 1      | **Superior Strength**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +4 strength  |\n| 3     | 1      | **Heroic Strength**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +6 strength    |\n| 4     | 2      | **Absolute Strength**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +10 strength |\n"},{"name":"Vitality","path":"Brick Power/Vitality.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                             |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Enhanced Vitality 1**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +2 durability  |\r\n| 2     | 1      | **Enhanced Vitality 2**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +4 durability  |\r\n| 3     | 1      | **Enhanced Vitality 3**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +6 durability  |\r\n| 4     | 2      | **Enhanced Vitality 4**\u003cbr\u003eGives you +10 durability |"},{"name":"Bombard","path":"Effector/Bombard.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                 |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **OmniBlast**\u003cbr\u003e-You explode causing 1d8 damage to everything around you. You can choose the damage type of the blast. |\r\n\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Disaster","path":"Effector/Disaster.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                                                             |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Seismic**\u003cbr\u003e-The land around you shakes causing enemies to fall prone and take 1d4 damage. They fall on a failed reflex check of 6. This affect happens to everyone but you in a 3 block radius. |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Meteor**\u003cbr\u003e-Summon a asteroid that falls on an enemy. The meteor does 1d20 damage to everything in a 20m radius.                                                                                 |\r\n"},{"name":"Elemental Control","path":"Effector/Elemental Control.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Terrain Molder**\u003cbr\u003e-You can make walls out of your element of choice.\u003cbr\u003e-Fire: Deal 1d4 damage and cause burning when moved through\u003cbr\u003e-Water: Slow movement by half when move through\u003cbr\u003e-Earth: Can not be moved through and have 6 armor\u003cbr\u003e-Air: Can not be moved or attacked through. Invisible. |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Tentacles!**\u003cbr\u003e-You can summon tentacles made out of your element. Can grapple enemies from a distance and keep then restrained.\u003cbr\u003e-Water: Deal 1d4 true damage\u003cbr\u003e-Fire: Deal 1d4 and cause burning\u003cbr\u003e-Air: Deal 1d4 and are invisible\u003cbr\u003e-Earth: Deal 1d6 and have 6 armor\u003cbr\u003e                     |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Elemental Blasts**\u003cbr\u003e-You can fire blasts of your element that deal 1d6 damage and a bonus effect.                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Florakinesis","path":"Effector/Florakinesis.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                              |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Binding 1**\u003cbr\u003e-You can cause grass to bind people\u0027s feet. You can cause this in a 20m range. This is a strength 7 check to escape |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Control 1**\u003cbr\u003e-You can control plants in a 10m radius                                                                             |\r\n"},{"name":"Laser","path":"Effector/Laser.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                    |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Laser Beam**\u003cbr\u003e-You deal 1d4 to anything in sight range |\r\n"},{"name":"Null","path":"Effector/Null.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                         |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Equalizer**\u003cbr\u003e-You can cause one person in your range to become baseline human. This affects both of you. Your range is 10m. |\r\n| 1     | 2      | **Negate**\u003cbr\u003e-You become immune to one damage type                                                                             |\r\n"},{"name":"Pocket Dimension","path":"Effector/Pocket Dimension.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                              |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Inventory**\u003cbr\u003e-You can store up to 3 items in a pocket dimension                                                                                  |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Domain**\u003cbr\u003e-You can make your pocket dimension overlap the land around you.\u003cbr\u003e-You chose what is inside the dimension when you choose this power |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Sillakinesis","path":"Effector/Sillakinesis.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                                                                           |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Glass Control**\u003cbr\u003e-You can shatter glass in a 50m radius on command.\u003cbr\u003e-You can control a stream of glass shards and cut things with them. They automatically hit in a 10m radius of you and deal 1d3 damage. |\n\n"},{"name":"Sound Manipulation","path":"Effector/Sound Manipulation.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                   |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Sonic Burst**\u003cbr\u003e-You deal 1d4 damage that ignores external armour to enemies within 5m |\r\n| 1     | 1      | Silence\u003cbr\u003e-You don\u0027t produce any sound unless you want to.                               |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Telekinesis","path":"Effector/Telekinesis.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                         |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Tactile telekinesis**\u003cbr\u003e-You can shove things in a 10m radius backwards 5m\u003cbr\u003e-You can do a smarts check instead of a strength check for any strength check. |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Telekinesis**\u003cbr\u003e-You can lift up to 3 objects or people in a 15m radius around you.                                                                          |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Transmute","path":"Effector/Transmute.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | Transmutation\u003cbr\u003e-You can transform one material into another for free |\r\n"},{"name":"Clairvoyant","path":"Genius/Clairvoyant.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                           |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **All seeing**\u003cbr\u003e-You see everything in a 10m radius around yourself.\u003cbr\u003e-This acts as truesight |\r\n"},{"name":"Social","path":"Genius/Social.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                     |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Enhanced Socials**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +2 Social |\r\n"},{"name":"Super Reflex","path":"Genius/Super Reflex.md","content":"\r\n| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                      |\r\n| ----- | ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Enhanced Reflexes**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +2 reflex                                                 |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Super Aim**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +3 to hitting enemies                                             |\r\n| 2     | 1      | **Killing Streak 1**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +1 damage after every successful hit.                      |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Bloodhound**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +8 to tracking if you have a trace of the thing you are tracking |\r\n"},{"name":"Super Smarts","path":"Genius/Super Smarts.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                           |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Enhanced Smarts**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +2 Smarts                                                        |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Doctorate**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain knowledge in a field of science and have advantage when it is relevant |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Omni Proficient**\u003cbr\u003eYou can use any tool and drive any vehicle                                 |\r\n"},{"name":"Mind Control","path":"Manipulator/Mind Control.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                 |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Taunt**\u003cbr\u003e-You force an enemy to focus on you for a turn. This is a free action.                                     |\n| 1     | 1      | **Puppeteer**\u003cbr\u003e-You make an enemies movement actions.                                                                 |\n| 1     | 1      | **Suggestion**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +4 to a persuasion check with a chance of being detected. The check is a smarts check of 8. |\n"},{"name":"Mitosis","path":"Manipulator/Mitosis.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                             |\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Clone 1**\u003cbr\u003e-You can create a cloned duplicate of yourself that has all your powers and follows your commands. It does not have the clone power. |\n"},{"name":"Statistician","path":"Manipulator/Statistician.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                            |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Lucky**\u003cbr\u003e-Once per turn order, you can make a roll into a double advantage     |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Unluck**\u003cbr\u003e-Once per turn order, you can make a roll into a double disadvantage |\r\n"},{"name":"Tide","path":"Manipulator/Tide.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                 |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Summon Tide minions**\u003cbr\u003e-You can summon [[Basic Tide Minions]]\u003cbr\u003e-You are capped to 5\u003cbr\u003e-They have -2 to all rolls |\n| 2     | 1      |                                                                                                                         |\n| 2     | 1      |                                                                                                                         |\n| 2     | 1      |                                                                                                                         |\n"},{"name":"Titan","path":"Manipulator/Titan.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                              |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Summon Titan**\u003cbr\u003e-You summon a large creature that has +2 to all rolls\u003cbr\u003e-You are capped to 1    |\r\n| 2     | 1      | **Titan Body 1**\u003cbr\u003e-Your Titan is made of stronger stuff.\u003cbr\u003e-Gain another +2 to armor and Strength |\r\n| 2     | 1      | **Titan Size**\u003cbr\u003e-Your Titan becomes massive. It\u0027s health and strength doubles                      |\r\n"},{"name":"Flight","path":"Movement/Flight.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                     |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Basic Flight**\u003cbr\u003e-You can move in any direction up to 5m and do not fall |\r\n"},{"name":"Rocket","path":"Movement/Rocket.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                    |\r\n| ----- | ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Basic Rocket**\u003cbr\u003e-You fly 5m in a straight line dealing 1d8 damage to whatever you hit and half that damage to yourself |\r\n"},{"name":"Skimmer","path":"Movement/Skimmer.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                            |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------ |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Skimmer**\u003cbr\u003e-You can move through difficult terrain unobstucted |\r\n"},{"name":"SuperSpeed","path":"Movement/SuperSpeed.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                   |\r\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Basic Superspeed**\u003cbr\u003e-Your movespeed is doubled to 20m |\r\n"},{"name":"Teleport (People)","path":"Movement/Teleport (People).md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                  |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Basic Teleport**\u003cbr\u003e-You can teleport yourself 10m instead of taking a movement action |\r\n"},{"name":"Cartoon","path":"Mutant/Cartoon.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                       |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Rubber and glue**\u003cbr\u003eYou take have immunity to blunt damage |\r\n"},{"name":"Elemental Body","path":"Mutant/Elemental Body.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                              |\r\n| ----- | ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Rock Body**\u003cbr\u003e-You can turn you body into stone. This gives you 2 armor and makes your melee attack a 1d6         |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Water Body**\u003cbr\u003e-You have resistance to slashing and piercing damage.                                              |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Flame Body**\u003cbr\u003e-Your unarmed melee attacks cause you to deal stacks of burning. You gain immunity to fire damage. |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Wind Body**\u003cbr\u003e-Your jump height doubles and you take no fall damage.                                              |\r\n"},{"name":"Feral","path":"Mutant/Feral.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                                            |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Cursed one basic**\u003cbr\u003eYou can switch to a mutated form that is visibly identifiable as an action. In this form you gain +1 to Ref ,Str and Armor but gain -1 to all other stats. |\r\n"},{"name":"Kaiju","path":"Mutant/Kaiju.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                       |\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Monstrous Size**\u003cbr\u003e-You become twice the size of a human\u003cbr\u003e-Your size gives you +2 strength when working on things smaller than you.      |\n| 2     | 1      | **Gaint Size**\u003cbr\u003e-You become four times the size of a human\u003cbr\u003e-Your size gives you +4 strength when working on things smaller than you.     |\n| 3     | 1      | **Titanic Size**\u003cbr\u003e-You become eight times the size of a human\u003cbr\u003e-Your size gives you +8 strength when working on things smaller than you.  |\n| 4     | 1      | **Kaiju Size**\u003cbr\u003e-You become sixteen times the size of a human\u003cbr\u003e-Your size gives you +16 strength when working on things smaller than you. |\n\n"},{"name":"Mutate","path":"Mutant/Mutate.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                 |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | You gain +1 strength every two turns of combat up to 5  |\r\n| 2     | 1      | You gain +1 strength every two turns of combat up to 10 |\r\n| 3     | 1      | You gain +2 strength every two turns of combat up to 20 |\r\n| 4     | 2      | You gain +4 strength every two turns of combat up to 20 |"},{"name":"Shapeshifter","path":"Mutant/Shapeshifter.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                     |\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Wildshape**\u003cbr\u003e-You can take the forms of animals smaller than humans but bigger than bugs. These have to be real animals |\n| 1     | 1      | **Changeling**\u003cbr\u003e-You can take the appearance of people you have seen before                                               |\n| 1     | 1      | **Natural Tools**\u003cbr\u003e-You can shift your body into tools and weapons on command                                             |\n"},{"name":"Thistle","path":"Mutant/Thistle.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                                                                                                                      |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Shell**\u003cbr\u003e-Enemies that attack you take 2 damage                                                                                                                                                          |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Hunker Down**\u003cbr\u003e-You can Hunker down as an action, Consuming all your movement and rooting you in place until your next turn. When in this state you gain 2 armor and when attack you deal 2 damage back. |\r\n\r\n"},{"name":"Vampire","path":"Mutant/Vampire.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                              |\r\n| ----- | ------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Lifesteal**\u003cbr\u003e-When you deal damage to an enemy heal for 4 health |\r\n"},{"name":"Action Hero","path":"Ranger/Action Hero.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                               |\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Hero\u0027s Limits**\u003cbr\u003e-Every 3rd shot with a gun doesn\u0027t take ammo                     |\n| 1     | 1      | **Scene Maker**\u003cbr\u003e-You can kick down doors with advantage                            |\n| 1     | 1      | **Last Stand**\u003cbr\u003eYou survive for 1 more turn after dying                             |\n| 2     | 1      | **Winner\u0027s Stand**\u003cbr\u003eYou can extend your time before dying by 1 if you kill an enemy |\n"},{"name":"Assassin","path":"Ranger/Assassin.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                           |\r\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Sneak Attack**\u003cbr\u003e-You deal double damage when attacking from stealth                                           |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Move unseen**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain advantage when sneaking                                                              |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Traceless**\u003cbr\u003e-You are untraceable unless you allow otherwise                                                  |\r\n| 1     | 1      | **Corpse Dust**\u003cbr\u003e-Things you kill fade to ashes before disappearing completely                                  |\r\n| 2     | 7      | **From Dust to Dust**\u003cbr\u003e-When you kill something or someone you can make them be forgotten from peoples memories |\r\n"},{"name":"Boomeranger","path":"Ranger/Boomeranger.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                 |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Boomerang**\u003cbr\u003eEvery item you throw can be returned to you.           |\n| 2     | 1      | **Ricochet 1**\u003cbr\u003e-Thrown items hit 2 enemies in range before returning |\n"},{"name":"Parry","path":"Ranger/Parry.md","content":"\n| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                                     |     |\n| ----- | ------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Basic Parry**\u003cbr\u003eYou can completely block an attack if you make a reflex check equal to the enemy roll -4 |     |\n| 2     | 1      | **Reflect**\u003cbr\u003eIf you roll 2 higher than the enemy they take half the damage the attack would have done.    |     |\n\n"},{"name":"Swordsman","path":"Ranger/Swordsman.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                                       |\n| ----- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Blade Warrior**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain +2 to hit and damage when attacking with a bladed melee weapon |\n| 2     | 1      | **Blade Master**\u003cbr\u003e-You gain advantage when attacking with a bladed weapon                   |\n"},{"name":"Wielder","path":"Ranger/Wielder.md","content":"| LEVEL | POINTS | ABILITY                                                                   |\n| ----- | ------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| 1     | 1      | **Unbreakable Weapon 1**\u003cbr\u003e-Items you touch gain 4 armour for 5 minutes  |\n| 2     | 1      | **Unbreakable Weapon 2**\u003cbr\u003e-Items you touch gain 8 armour for 5 minutes  |\n| 3     | 1      | **Unbreakable Weapon 3**\u003cbr\u003e-Items you touch gain 12 armour for 5 minutes |\n| 4     | 1      | **Unbreakable Weapon 4**\u003cbr\u003e-Items you touch gain 16 armour for 5 minutes |\n"},{"name":"Bio-Horror Techie","path":"Techie/Bio-Horror Techie.md","content":"\nOnly this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n# Lv1\n\nGene Synthesizer: A machine that spins junk DNA into the DNA of your choice.  \nCost: $100  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\n\n\nGene Implanter: A injection device.  \nCost: $100  \nEffect: Allows you to install a gene mod once per turn. A human can only have 5 gene mods at one time or penalties start to happen.  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nPortable Gene Scanner: A wand-style device that identifies biological material.\nCost: $50\nEffect: Reveals what species\u0027 DNA is present in any sample and whether itâ€™s viable for synthesis.\nRequirements: None\n\n\n---\n\n\nCat Mod: A gene mod made of cat DNA.  \nCost: 1kg of Cat flesh or blood.  \nEffect: After Implantation it allows the player to see in the dark and makes the player immune to fall damage.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\n\nBat Mod: A gene mod made of bat DNA.  \nCost: 1kg of Bat flesh or blood.  \nEffect: After Implantation it allows the player to see in a 20m radius with blindsight.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\n\nBird Mod: A gene mod made of bird DNA  \nCost: 1kg of bird flesh or blood.  \nEffect: After Implantation it allows the player to grow wings and fly.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\n\nCrab mod: A gene mod made of Crab DNA  \nCost: 1kg of crab flesh or blood.  \nEffect: After Implantation it forces the player to grow a crab claw which gives you a 1d8 melee dice and you grow armor plates that give you 1 armor.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\n\nLobster mod: A gene mod made of lobster DNA  \nCost: 1kg of lobster flesh or blood.  \nEffect: After Implantation the player stops aging and instead the player grows larger every year.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\n\nSpider mod: A gene mod made of spider DNA  \nCost: 1kg of spider flesh or ichor.  \nEffect: After Implantation the player can climb wall and his bite deals 3d4 poison damage after 3 turns.  \nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\n\nLizard mod: A gene mod made of general reptile DNA.\nCost: 1kg of reptile flesh or blood.\nEffect: After Implantation the player becomes invisible to infrared and starts regenerating 1 Hp per turn.\nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\nRat Mod: A gene mod made of rodent DNA\n\nCost: 1kg rat flesh or blood\nEffect: Advantage on stealth; immune to disease; squeeze through tiny holes\nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n\n---\nDog Mod â€” NEW\n\nCost: 1kg canine flesh or blood\nEffect: Super-smell (track targets within 2km), +2 initiative\nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\nJellyfish Mod â€” NEW\n\nCost: 1kg jellyfish tissue\nEffect: Gain electroreceptors (sense movement in water), and touch deals 1d6 electric damage\nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n---\nBeetle Mod â€” NEW\n\nCost: 1kg beetle tissue\nEffect: Hardened exoskeletal patches grant +2 armor\nRequirements: Gene Synthesizer\n\n# Lv2â€Œ\n\n  \nGene Cocoon: A large mechanical pod like device. Used to make creatures from dna strands.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Allows for the creation of creatures with gene mods.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\n[[Bio Horror Imp]]: A small crafty creature.\n\n[[Bio Horror Grunt]]:\n\n[[Bio Horror Troll]]:"},{"name":"Chemical Techie","path":"Techie/Chemical Techie.md","content":"This ability allows the player to build Tinker Chemicals. Only this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n  \n# Lv1  \n\nBodysuits: This suit protects the wearer from chemicals and diseases.  \nCost: $10  \nEffects: Grants immunity to all chemical and biological attacks.  \nRequirements: None\n\n----\nHyperGlue: A sticky substance that is a extremely powerful adhesive.  \nCost: $10 per use  \nEffect: When a person or object touches this substance they are stuck to it for 20 turns.  \nRequirements: None\n\n----\nBoost Tonic: A sickly sweat substance that boosts one of your attributes.  \nCost: $100  \nEffect: Roll 1D20 on anything but a 1 you gain 1D4 of the stat of your choice. On a 1 you take 1D4 damage. Lasts 50 turns.  \nRequirements: None \n\n----\nBasic Chemical Workbench: A small bench with a distillery and some beakers.  \nCost: $100  \nRequirements: None\n\n----\nPiranha Juice: A chemical that eats through exposed flesh.\nCost: $100\nEffects: Deal 1D10 damage to an enemy. If they are unarmored, double this damage.\nRequirements: Basic Chemical workbench.\nâ€Œ\n\n----\nSubstance Sprayer: A gun with a long nozzle that can spray substances up to 100m.\nCost: $100\nEffects: Increases range of all substances to 100m.\nRequirements: Basic Chemical workbench.\n\n---\nBasic Biohazard Mech Suit: A airtight mechsuit that can still fit inside of buildings.\nCost: $100  \nHP: 100  \nMovespeed: 15m per turn  \nArmor: 2  \nSubstance Slots: 2  \nEffects: Can Carty 10 stacks of 2 different Chemicals. Completely Airtight and functions as a basic Chemical Workbench. Increases strength to 10.\nRequirements: Mech Suit Tinker Lv 1\n\n---\nInstant Pitfall: A corrosive chemical that doesn\u0027t dissolve organic matter.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Creates a 20m deep hole at location it was thrown.\nRequirements: Fortification Tinker Lv 1\n\n---\n# Lv2  \n\nEnhanced Molotov: A Molotov cocktail that was made with a similar composition to Napalm and White Phosphorous.  \nCost: $10  \nEffects: Lights a 10m area on fire. The fire lasts 2 hours.  \nDamage: 1 damage per turn.  \nRequirements: Basic Chemical Workbench.\n\n---\nEyeSolver: A spray the is slightly acidic but is very aerosolized and disperses well over an area.\nCost: $100\nEffects: Causes blinding.\nDamage: 1\nRequirements: Basic Chemical Workbench.\n\n---\nMindwipe: A viscous fluid that tastes like the color purple. It wipes the mind of whoever drinks it.\nCost: $100\nEffects: Removes 1 days worth of memories after being ingested.\nDamage: None\nRequirements: Basic Chemical Workbench.\n\n---\nChemical Workbench: A big bench with advanced chemical equipment. Used to make better chemicals and items.\nCost: $1000\nRequirements: Basic Chemical Workbench.\n\n---\nGas Cloud: A chemical that spreads other a massive area and is mildly toxic.\nCost: $1000\nEffects: Spreads- spreads over a 1km area. Lasts 2 days.\nDamage: 1 damage per hour.\nRequirements: Chemical workbenchâ€Œ.\n\n---\nChemical grenades: A small metal ball that violently sprays chemicals in a area around it.\nCost: $1000 Reusable\nEffect: Sprays the loaded chemical in a 20m area.\nRequirements: Chemical workbench.\n\n---\nFluJuice: A vial of concentrated flu virus.\nCost: $10000\nEffect: Instantly takes effect and gives the target the flu.\nRequirements: Chemical workbench.\n\n---\n# Lv3  \n\nAnthrax Gamma: A vial of Death. DO NOT USE ON ALLIES.  \nCost: $10000  \nEffect: Deals 1D4 damage per 12 hours unless treated.\nRequirements: Chemical workbench.\n\n---\nChemical Workshop: A upgrade to a building that makes it airtight and allows you to make advanced chemicals.\nCost: $100000\nRequirements: Chemical workbench.\n\n---\nResurrection Serum: A practically magic fluid that encourages regeneration and restores brain function.\nCost: $100000\nEffect: Returns a target from death and heals them to full.\nRequirements: Chemical Workshop\n\n---\nZombie Virus: A chemical that turns corpses into zombies that target the nearest enemies with melee attacks.\nCost: $100000\nEffect: Turns a corpse into a zombie that attacks the living. The zombie spreads the virus by hitting someone. Zombies have a -5 to all rolls.\nRequirement: Chemical Workshop.\n\n---\nAdvanced Stat Serum: A overpoweringly sour tasting chemical. Permanently boosts a stat.\nCost: $100000\nEffect: Boosts a random stat by 1D4 permanently\nRequirement: Chemical Workshop.\n\n---\n# Lv4  \n\nYou can only choose one level four item to build. You an build as many as you want.\n\n---\nACDC: Advanced chemical dispersal circuit. Helps spread chemicals.\nCost: $1000000\nEffect: Allows you to apply a single chemical to the entire city\nRequirements: Chemical Workshop.\n\n---\nPower Serum: A chemical that tastes, smells and looks like death. Unlocks random superpowers for person.\nCost: $1000000\nEffect: Gives a unpowered person 1 point worth of powers chosen randomly.\nRequirements: Chemical Workshop."},{"name":"Divine Techie","path":"Techie/Divine Techie.md","content":"This ability allows the player to build Tinker Weapons that switch between forms and operate of off exotic energy. Only this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n  \n\n# Lv1  \n\n---\nAegis of Athena: A fancy round shield. It has grooves and ridges along its face.  \n\nCost: $10000  \nEffect: While worn it grants +4 armor. You have -2 to reflex. It can transform into Bow of Artemis.  \nRange: Melee  \nDamage: 1D4  \nRequirement: none\n\n---\nBow of Artemis: A fancy bow. It looks thick and sturdy.  \n\nCost: $10000  \nEffect: This weapon ignores 4 armor. You get -2 to Smarts. It can transform into Shield of Athena  \nRange: 75m  \nDamage: 1d12  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nGreat Axe of Ares: A massive 2 handed axe. It has a seem in the middle.  \n\nCost: $10000.01  \nEffect: Damage increases by +1 for every 30 enemies slain. Can Transform into Hand Axes of Enyu.  \nRange: Melee  \nDamage: 1d6  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nHand Axes of Enyu: A pair of handaxes, they seem to make parts of a bigger whole.  \n\nCost: $10000.01  \nEffect: Heal 2 health on every hit, gain +1 to this effect for every 30 enemies slain. Can Transform into Great Axe of Ares.  \nRange: Melee  \nDamage: 1d4 each  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nStaff of Dionysus  \n\nCost: $10000.02  \nEffect: When an enemy is hit. Temporarily reduce their Smarts by 2. Can transform into Whip of Aphrodite.  \nRange: Melee  \nDamage: 1d4  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nWhip of Aphrodite  \n\nCost: $10000.02  \nEffect: When a character is whipped. Temporarily increase their social by 2. Can transform into Staff of Dionysus.  \nRange: Melee  \nDamage: 1d4  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nRing of Apollo  \n\nCost: $10000.03  \nEffect: Gives the wearer +3 to social. The wearer has -3 to durability while wearing. Can Transform into Ring of Eris.  \nRequirements: none\n\n---\nRing of Eris  \n\nCost: $10000.03  \nEffect: You can reroll 1 enemy roll per round. The wearer gets -3 to social while wearing. Can Transform into Ring of Apollo.\n\n# Lv2\n\n---\nMace of Zeus:\n\n\nCost: $20000\n\nEffect: When you hit an enemy and an ally hits them after, the enemy takes damage equal to the amount of times this effect has been applied, Applied Additively. Can transform into a Bastard Sword of Hades\n\nRange: Melee\n\nDamage: 1d4\n\nRequirements: noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nBastard Sword of Hades:\n\n\nCost: $20000\n\nEffect: You can mark a target once in combat. This target can now only damage you and be damaged by you. When the enemy dies they can be resummoned as a ghost with 1 in every stat and their powers at 1 tenth strength. Can transform into Mace of Zeus\n\nRange Melee\n\nDamage: 1d6\n\nRequirements: noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nShuriken\u0027s of Achlys: Golden Triangles to throw at your enemies.\n\n\nCost: $20000.08\n\nEffect: Poisons an enemy hit to take 1 damage per turn forever. Can Transform into a Staff of Asclepius\n\nRange: 50m\n\nDamage: 1d4\n\nRequirements: noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nStaff of Asclepius: A golden staff with twin snakes on each side.\n\n\nCost: $20000.08\n\nEffect: Can be used to remove every debuff from an ally and heal them for 1d4, this effect need to be used as a action. Can transform into the Shuriken\u0027s of Achlys\n\nRange: 20m\n\nDamage: 1d4\n\nRequirements: noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nReVoLvEr Of KoAs: A dArK bLaCk ReVoLvEr, RaInBoW eNeEgY lEaKs FrOm It.\n\n\nCost: None\n\nEffect: Must be found and can not be built. When you shoot an enemy you roll a 1d100. The DM decides what the bullet does.\n\nRange: 100m\n\nDamage: 1d10\n\nRequirements: noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nGreaves of Hermes: A pair of Armored Thigh high Leg bracers.\n\n\nCost: $20000.07\n\nEffect: You go one higher in the initiative order. You get 1 free turn before the combat begins. You move faster than your party members. Can Transform into Fingerless Gloves of Chronos.\n\nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nFingerless Gloves of Chronos: A pair of Hot Pink Fingerless Gloves.\n\n\nCost: $20000.07\n\nEffect: Provides hidden bonus. Every second attack moves an enemy 1 step down in the initiative order.\n\nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n# Lv3  \n\n---\nBook of the Athenian Dolomite: A Golden book wreathed in shadows.  \n\nCost: $30000.1  \nEffect: You may ask the book any question. The DM then secretly rolls 1d4. On a 1 the book gives the truth. On a 2 or 3 the book gives 42 and 24 unrespectivly. On a 4 the book gives a believable lie.  \nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nAxe of Bloody Matrimony: A blood red Greataxe. It seems to bleed more than its enemies.\n\n\nCost: $10000, Greataxe of Ares, Hand Axes of Enyu\n\nEffect: Gain +1 damage and +2 healing with every 15 enemies slain. The Axe Heals for 2 on every hit.\n\nRange: Melee\n\nDamage: 1d12\n\nRequirements: None\n\nâ€Œ\n\n---\nRing of Choatic Friendship: A golden glowing band covered in snakes that seem to roam across the ring.\n\n\nCost: $10000, Ring of Eris, Ring of Apollo\n\nEffect: You can give 1 ally advantage to rolls for the round or reroll 3 enemies rolls. It also gives +3 to social.\n\nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ"},{"name":"Fire Techie","path":"Techie/Fire Techie.md","content":"\nOnly this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n\n# Lv1\n\nIgnition Gloves: A pair of fire proof gloves with a lighter built in.\nCost: $10\nEffects: Can ignite materials with touch. Reduces taken fire damage by 1.\nRequirements: None\n\n\n---\nFirestarter Paste: A thick paste made of flammable materials that burn for a long time.\nCost: $10\nEffects: Burns for 10 turns doing 1 damage per turn. Waterproof.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nFlashfuel Bottle: A small capsule filled with a volatile liquid.\nCost: $50\nEffects: Creates a 5m radius blast of light and fire. Deals 1d4 damage. Targets must make a reflex check of 5 or be blinded for 1 turn.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nBasic Pyrotechnics Bench: A metal bench with ignition chambers, pressurized tanks, and controlled flame nozzles.\nCost: $100\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nIncendiary Gel: A sticky gel that burns brightly\nCost: $100\nEffects: Does 1d6 damage when thrown. Burns for 3 turns doing 1d4 damage a turn. Waterproof\nRequirements: Basic Pyrotechnics Bench\n\n---\nFlame Nozzle: A weak flamethrower that can launch your chemicals further.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Increases the effective range of your chemicals to 20m.\nRequirements: Basic Pyrotechnics Bench\n\n---\nFlame Suit: A insulated suit filled with fireproof materials.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Reduces taken fire damage by 4.\n\n---\nThermite Bomb: A large bundle of vials and packages with wires coming out of it.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Causes an 10m explosion that coats everything in range with thermite. Coated enemies take 1d10 fire damage per turn for 10 turns."},{"name":"Fortification Techie","path":"Techie/Fortification Techie.md","content":"A tinker that can fortify buildings and locations with gun turrets and walls.\n\n  \n\n---\n# Lv1\n\n\n---\nReinforced Bodysuit: A skintight bodysuit with reinforced inlays.  \nCost: $10  \nEffect: Gain +2 armor.  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nConcrete Sprayer: A gun with a tank that constantly makes concrete.  \nCost: $10  \nEffects: Allows you to build walls or seal of doors in 1 turn. The walls have 20HP and 3 armor.  \nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nConcrete Foam Grenade: A small tank to foam that can harden to the strength of rock.\nCost: $10\nEffects: Seal 5m area in concrete. The foam has no armor and only has 10hp.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nFort Workbench: Allows you to build basic fortifications.  \nCost: $100  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nAutoTurret: A small gun turret that can be deployed in 1 turn.\nCost: $100\nHp:5\nSize: 1/2 slot  \nEffects: Automatically attacks the nearest enemy.  \nDamage: 1D4  \nRange: 50m  \nRequirements: Fort Workbench.\n\n---\nDuel Turret: A gun turret with 2 barrels. Takes 2 turns to deploy.  \nCost: $500\nHp:10\nSize: 1/2 slot  \nEffects: Automatically attacks the nearest enemy.  \nDamage: 2D4  \nRange: 50m  \nRequirements: Fort Workbench.\n\n---\nReinforced Wall: A upgrade to any existing wall to make it tougher to destroy.  \nCost: $100  \nEffects: Increase a walls health to 50 and it armor to 6  \nRequirements: Concrete Sprayerâ€Œ\n\n---\nEntrenching Tool: A hyper advanced digging tool.\nCost: $100\nEffect: Allows the player to dig a cubic meter every turn.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nCatapult Trap: A permanent stationary trap.\nCost: $100\nEffect: Launches mooks/civvies up to 1d10 x10 meters if stepped on. Can only activate once per turn.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nTar Pit Trap: A permanent stationary trap\nCost: $100\nEffect: If a person is standing on the trap, they lose half of their actions\nRequirements: Chemical Tinker Lv 1\n\n---\nCorrosive Gas Turret: A permanent stationary trap\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Releases Piranha juice on everything that passes it.\nRequirements: Chemical Tinker Lv 1\n\n---\nFortified Basic Mech Suit:\nCost: $1000  \nHP: 50  \nMovespeed: 15m per turn  \nArmor: 2  \nTurret Slots: 2  \nEffects: Doubles production speed for bigger mechs. (Doesn\u0027t stack) Increases strength to 10. Too Bulky to use normal or mech weapons. There is 1/5 chance that enemies hit the player instead of the mech. You can\u0027t deploy turrets from inside the mech. If equipped with a quick deploy mod instead of 1 turret you can deploy turrets from inside.\nRequirements: Mech Tinker Lv1â€Œ\n\n---\nShoulder mounted Machine Gun: A Browning machine gun strapped to a auto aiming system.\nCost: $500\nHp: 10\nSize: 1 slot\nRange: 50m\nEffect: Targets Nearest enemy.\nDamage: 3d8\nRequirement: Mech tinker Lv 1\n\n---\nSize mod: Decreases the size of a turret by half.  \nCost: $1000  \nEffect: Halves size of a turret.  \nRequirements: Gadget tinker Lv 1.â€Œ\n\n---\nQuick Deploy Mod: Allows for quick Deployment of turrets.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Allows for the deployment of two turrets a turn.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nTurret Platform Drone: A large platform with propellers.\nCost: $1000\nHp: 20\nEffect: This drone can carry 4 lv 1 turrets or 1 Lv 2 turret on it. It can also fly.\nRequirements: Interface tinker.\n\n---\n# Lv2\n\n---\nEmplaced Turret: A more permanent automatic defense. Stronger than the AutoTurret. Takes 1 hour to deploy.  \nCost: $500\nHp:20\nSize: 1 slot  \nEffect: Automatically attacks the nearest enemy. Needs 1 day to remove from emplaced position.\nDamage: 1D8  \nRange: 100m  \nRequirement: Fort Workbench.â€Œ\n\n---\nStealth Mod: Upgrade a turret to be stealthed while inactive.\nCost: add half of price to item.â€Œ\n\n---\nArmor Mod: Give a item 5 Hp and 5 armor.\nCost: Double Cost of Item.â€Œ\n\n---\nDart Trap: A permanent upgrade to a wall that lets it fire tranq darts.\nCost: $500\nEffect: Automatically attacks any enemies that step in front of it. On a failed Durability roll of 5 the enemy is knocked out.\nRange: 20m\nRequirement: Fort Workbench.â€Œ\n\n---\nHologram projector: A small device the size of a brick. Can create non-solid illusions.\nCost: $500\nHp:5\nSize: 1/2 slot\nEffect: Can project 1 non-solid illusion at a time. These illusions are destroyed if the projector is destroyed.\nRange: 100m\nRequirement: Fort Workbench.â€Œ\n\n---\nFort Workshop: A upgrade to any room. Allows you to build more advanced turrets and fortifications.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Allows for more advanced projects and fortifications.\nRequirement: Fort Workbench.â€Œ\n\n---\nAT Turret: A massive immoveable turret made to destroy vehicles.\nCost: $1000\nHp:50\nSize: 1 slot\nEffect: Targets nearest enemy vehicle.\nDamage: 1D12\nRange: 200m\nEffect: Ignores armor.\nRequirements: Fort Workshop.â€Œ\n\n---\nArtillery Turret: A massive gun that shoot to hit via an arc.\nCost: $1000\nHp: 30\nSize: 1 slot\nEffect: Can only shoot at artillery markers. Fires upon a artillery marker when activated. Deals 1d6 damage in a 25m radius. Doesn\u0027t need line of sight to attack.\nRange: 1km\nRequirements: Fort workshopâ€Œ\n\n---\nArtillery Marker: A hand sized device that activates the artillery turret.\nCost: $100\nEffect: Is targeted by artillery turrets in range when activated. Allows for specifications when deployed by the tinker.\nRange: 1km\nRequirements: Fort workshop.â€Œ\n\n---\nLethal Mod: Adjusts Auto and Duel Turrets to use lethal bullets.\nCost: 2x cost of item.\nEffect: Doubled the damage of a turret, but the turrets can now cause death by attacking.\nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nCatapult Turret (small): Launches loaded items.\nCost: $1000\nSize: 1 slot\nRange: 400m\nDamage: 1d8\nEffect: Launches items.\nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nCatapult Turret (large): Launches loaded items.  \nCost: $10000\nSize: 2 slots  \nRange: 1km  \nDamage: 1d20  \nEffect: Launches items.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshopâ€Œ\n\n---\nBlazing Mod: Adjust a turret to cause burning on hit.\nCost: 3x cost of item.\nEffect: Targets hit by a turret with this mod is set ablaze for 3 turns, causing 1d8 damage per turn. This damage is lethal.\nRequirements: Chemical Tinker Lv 2.â€Œ\n\n---\nMech Deployment Canon: A massive Gun emplacement that can fire Basic mechs\nCost: $10000\nRange: 1km\nEffect: Allows the player to deploy a basic mech to a target in range.\nRequirements: Mech Tinker Lv 2.â€Œ\n\n---\nRecall Mod: Allows the player to recall auto or dual turrets to him instantly.\nCost: $1000\nEffect when installed on a turret it allows the player to teleport turrets back to them.\nRequirements: Gadget tinker Lv 2.\n\n---\nWeakness Identifier mod: Allows the turret to find weaknesses in enemies,\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Adds a flat 4 damage to the turret it is installed on.\nRequirements: Interface Tinker Lv 2 and a active brain case.\n  \n\n---\n# Lv3\n\n\n---\nLaser Turret: A industry grade laser mounted in a focusing lens.  \nCost: $10000\nHp: 10\nSize: 2 slots  \nRange: Line of sight  \nDamage:1d8 per turn  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nForcefield Projector: A small device that gives a set target a forcefield when attacked.  \nCost: $10000\nHp: 5\nSize: 1 slot  \nRange: 100m  \nEffect: Blocks 5 attacks of any strength for a set target. Needs 1 hour to recharge after use.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop.\n\n---\nHardlight Projector: A device that allows the player to make solid illusions.  \nCost:$10000\nHp: 5\nSize: 1 slot  \nRange: 100m  \nEffect: Can create up to 5 solid illusions with 10hp and no armor.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nHeavy Armor Mod: Allows the player to modify items with more hitpoints and some armor.  \nCost: Quadruple the cost of a item.  \nEffect: Add 10 Hp to a item and give it 10 armor.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nBurrow Mod: Allows the player to modify items to hide underground when not attacking.  \nCost: 5x cost of item  \nEffect: Item becomes invincible when not active.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nRepair Drone: A drone that can heal your items.  \nCost: $100000  \nEffect: Repairs items in the room they are installed in. Heals 2hp every turn.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop.\n\n---\nLaser wall/door: A wall or door made of deadly lasers. Need a access code to disable.  \nCost: $10000  \nEffect: Deals 10d10 damage to anything that tries to move past it.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nDamage Mod: Doubles the damage of a item.  \nCost: 2x the items cost.  \nEffect: damage of item 2x  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop\n\n---\nQuick Deploy mod: Halves the deploy time of items.  \nCost: 4x the items cost.  \nEffect: Halves the deploy time of items.  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop.\n\n---\n# Lv4\n\n\n---\nOnly one of the following can be built.\n\n\n---\nB.L.A.M. Canon: Ballistic Landmark Assisted by Markers. An Utterly massive gun emplacement the size of a small building.  \nCost: $1000000  \nEffect: Uses Artillery markers to get accurate coordinates for bombardment. Shells are Built separately. A shell does 10d10 damage to everything in a 200 meter radius. Shells Cost $10000  \nRange: 100km  \nRequirements: Fort Workshop. Needs a buildings worth of space to build.â€Œ\n\n---\nTechnocrete: A upgrade for all concrete you make. Filled with titanium\nCost: $100000\nEffect: All concrete has 100hp and 10 armor.\nRequirements: Fort Workbench."},{"name":"Gadget Techie","path":"Techie/Gadget Techie.md","content":"This ability allows the player to build Tinker Gadgets. Only this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n# Lv1\n\n---\nArmored Tuxedo: A impressive looking suit that has armor plates sown into it.\n\nCost: $100\nEffect: Gain +2 armor\nRequirements: Noneâ€Œ\n\n---\nConcealed Knife: A knife concealed as a item of the players choice.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nRange: Touch\n\nDamage: 1d6\n\nEffect: Can do lethal damage.\n\nRequirements: None.â€Œ\n\n---\nTranquillizer dart: A small concealable dart of tranquillizer.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nRange: Touch or thrown\n\nDamage: None\n\nEffect: Enemy makes a durability check. Below a 6 causes them to be knocked out.\n\nRequirements: None.â€Œ\n\n---\nSuitcase Workbench: A suitcase that contains all the tools needed to make more complex gadgets.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nEffect: Allows for more complex gadgets.\n\nRequirements: None[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nBoot Concealed Bo staff: A collapsible bo staff that fits into the sole of a boot.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nRange: 5m\n\nDamage: 1d8\n\nRequirements: Suitcase Workbench.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nBasic Exosuit: A skintight mechsuit that offers minor assistance.\n\n\nCost: $1000\n\nHp: 40\n\nArmor: 2\n\nGadget slots: 2\n\nEffect: Boosts strength by 4. Can have 2 gadgets built into it.\n\nRequirements: Mech Suit Tinker Lv 1[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nConcealed Wrist Gas Spray: A tiny single use Gas can.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nEffect: Spray a single substance up to 5m.\n\nRequirements: Chemical Tinker.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nMini Turret: A tiny turret used to distract enemies.\n\n\nCost: $10\n\nHp: 2\n\nDamage: 1 per turn.\n\nRequirements: Fort Tinker Lv 1[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nNerve Disruptor: A bomb that targets nerves with electricity.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nEffect: One time use. Stuns enemies in a 5m radius for 3 turns.\n\nRequirements: Interface Tinker Lv 1.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n  \n\n# Lv 2\n\n\n---\nCeramic Collapsible gun: A small pistol that can\u0027t be detected by metal detectors.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nRange: 20m\n\nDamage: 1d10\n\nRequirements: Suitcase Workbench\n\n[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nMulti Taser: A semi automatic taser.\n\n\nCost: $100\n\nRange: 10m\n\nDamage: 1d8 Non lethal damage.\n\nEffect: Can be shot twice per action.\n\nRequirement: Suitcase Workshop\n\n[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nViolin Case rocket Launcher: A rocket launcher disguised as a violin case.\n\n\nCost: $1000\n\nRange: 100m\n\nDamage: 1d20 in a 5m radius.\n\nRequirement: Suitcase Workshop\n\n[br]â€Œ"},{"name":"Interface Techie","path":"Techie/Interface Techie.md","content":"This ability allows the player to build Tinker Chemicals. Only this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n# Lv 1  \n\n\n---\nControl Helmet: A helmet that pushes metal rods into the brain of the wearer. Lets them control Interface tech.  \n\nCost: $100  \nControl Slots: 3  \nEffect: Allows the wearer to control compatible technology.  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nHover Drone: Cheap but Expendable drones.  \n\nCost: $50  \nHp: 2  \nEffect: Can fly.  \nItem Slot: 1  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nTaser: A small cheap non-lethal weapon.  \n\nCost: $10  \nDamage: 1d4 non lethal  \nRange: 10m  \nRequirements: None\n\n---\nRemote Workshop: A room that can be remote controlled to build items.  \n\nCost: $200  \nEffect: Allows for the production of more advanced items.  \nRequirements: None.\n\n---\nAudiovisual Kit: Allows you to see and hear through you drones.  \n\nCosts: $100  \nEffect: Allows for sight and hearing through a equipped drone.  \nRequirements: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nCar drone: A tiny car that can slip under doors.  \n\nCost: $50  \nHp: 2  \nEffect: Fits under doors.  \nItem slot: 1  \nRequirements: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nChemical Tank: A capsule that contains the players chemical of choice for chemical tinker catalogue.  \n\nCost: $50  \nEffect: Can be attached to drones. Releases the chemical on command.  \nRequirements: Chemical Tinker lv 1\n\n---\nTurret drone: A small turret that runs on its legs.  \n\nCost: $200  \nHp: 5  \nDamage: 1d4 per turn  \nRange: 50m  \nRequirements: Fort tinker Lv 1\n\n---\nPuppeteer Drone: A exoskeleton that can clamp to unwilling targets.  \n\nCost: $500  \nHp: 10  \nArmor: 1  \nEffect: Can attach to unconscious human targets to puppet them around. Still active after their awake.\nRequirement: Mech Tinker Lv 1â€Œ\n\n---\nRoller Drone: Small ball like drones. They fit under doors.\n\nCost: $200\nHp:4\nArmor: 3\nEffect: Can fit under doors. Can trip enemies that set on them.\nRequirement: Gadget Tinker.â€Œ\n\n---\n# Lv2  \n\n\n\n---\nBrain Extractor: A chair that looks suspiciously like a dentist chair.  \n\nCost: $1000  \nEffect: Removes brain from a target unconscious human and puts them in brain cases.  \nRequirement: Remote workshop\n\n---\nBrain Case: A jar with life support systems.  \n\nCost: $1000  \nEffect: Sustains a contained brain. Can be equipped with a Audiovisual system and a Control Helmet.  \nRequirement: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nControl booster: Lets you set automatic commands for drones.  \n\nCost: $1000  \nEffect: When equipped to a brain case with a brain. It lets the player set automatic controls for up to 10 drones.  \nRequirement: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nCase Carrier: A set of tank tracks with a drone controller.  \n\nCost: $100  \nHp: 10  \nMovespeed: 5m per turn  \nEffect: Can carry 1 brain case and move it freely.  \nRequirement: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nHypnotizer: A ray gun that affects the targets brain.  \n\nCost: $1000  \nRange: 10m  \nEffect: Roll 1d10, on a 8 or higher a mook is hypnotized and falls unconscious.  \nRequirements: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nBrain Clone: Wipe the memories of a brain and implant your own.\n\nCost: 1 Occupied Brain Case.\nEffect: Gives the player a second chance at live if they die. Stays inactive until current brain expires.\nRequirements: 1 Occupied Brain Case.\n\n---\nNerve Disruptor: Causes paralysis in a target creature.  \n\nCost: $1000  \nRange: 20m  \nDamage: None  \nEffect: Causes paralysis in target enemy on a roll higher than 5.  \nRequirements: Remote Workshop\n\n---\nKnockout Gas: A very potent necrotic in gas form.  \n\nCost: $100  \nEffect Single use. Knocks out every one in a 5m radius unless they roll higher than 8 on a durability check.  \nRequirement: Chemical tinker Lv 2\n\n---\nDisrupter turret: A turret equipped with a nerve disrupter.  \n\nCost: $1000\nRange: 20m\nEffect: Automatically targets enemies nearby. Causes paralysis in target enemy on a roll higher than 5.  \nRequirement: Fort Tinker Lv 2\n\n---\nMecha Carrier: A bipedal mech that can carry brains.\n\nCost: $1000\nHp: 100\nArmor: 4\nWeapon Slots: 1\nEffect: Gain all original stats. Allows brains to use hands. Can use mech weapons.  \nRequirement: Mech Tinker Lv 2\n\n---\nNeural Chips: A chip that can be implanted in unsuspecting people.\n\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Take control of a mook or civvy over a 12 hour period.\nRequirement: Gadget Tinker Lv 2\n\n  \n---\n# Lv 3  \n\n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \n  \nLv 4"},{"name":"Mech Techie","path":"Techie/Mech Techie.md","content":"This ability allows the player to build mechsuits. Only this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n  \n\n  ****\nLv1\n---\n\n\n**Bodysuit**: A skintight bodysuit that doesn\u0027t provide any protection. Makes you look slightly cooler. Necessary to use any of the mechs.\n\nCost: $10\n\nRequirements: none[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Big Pistol**: A Comically large pistol that can be stored inside mechs as a emergency sidearm.\n\nCost: $10\n\nRange: 10m\n\nDamage: 1D10\n\nRequirements: None[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Mech Rifle**: A massive gun that is made to be used by the mechs. The gun can still be used by people but only as a 2 handed weapon.\n\nCost: $100\n\nDamage: nD10 n = to the size of the mech that is being used. n = 1 is no mech.\n\nRange: 100m\n\nRequirements: None[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Ram**: A melee weapon that can take a beating. Mostly made of cheap materials like concrete and metal.\n\nCost: $100\n\nDamage: 1D6 + Strength\n\nRange: Touch\n\nRequirements: None[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Mech Workbench**: A bench with tools to build cheap mechsuits and better weapons. Needs 1 hour to pack or unpack.\n\nCost: $100\n\nRequirements: None[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Basic Mechsuit**: A small mechsuit that seats 1 person and still fits through normal doors. Basically just there to help build bigger mechs or carry heavy objects/weapons.\n\nCost: $100\n\nHP: 50\n\nMovespeed: 15m per turn\n\nArmor: 1\n\nWeapon slots: 2\n\nEffects: Doubles production speed for bigger mechs. (Doesn\u0027t stack) Can carry Mech weapons one handed. Increases strength to 10. There is a 1/4 chance that the enemy hits the player instead of the mech.\n\nRequirements: Mech Workbench.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Flamethrower**: A barrel to launch liquid pain at your enemies with.\n\nCost: $500\n\nRange:10m\n\nDamage: 1d4 in a 10m cone.\n\nEffect: Causes burning. Burning deals 1 damage per turn.\n\nRequirements: Mech Workbench[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Shield**: A massive Metal slab welded to the arm of a mech.\n\nCost: $500\n\nWeapon slots: 1\n\nEffect: +1 armor to your mech.\n\nRequirements: Mech Workbench[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Rotary Concrete Foam Launcher**: A grenade launcher that fires Concrete foam grenades.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nRange: 50m\n\nEffect: Launches Concrete foam grenades.\n\nRequirements: Fortification Tinker Lv 1[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Mech Sprayer**: A massive hose like sprayer built into a mech.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nEffect: Uses a Weapon slot. Allows the mech to contain and spray chemicals safely.\n\nRequirements: Chemical Tinker Lv 1Â \n\n---\n\n**Mulcher Mod**: A grinding mouth device that grinds organic waste into bio slurry.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nEffect: Turns organic waste into random bio-samples\n\nRequirements: Bio Horror Techie Lv 1\n\n\n\n---\nLv2\n---\n\n\n**Rocket Launcher**: A one time use weapon that fires unguided rocket. The rocket can be replaced during a short rest.  \nCost: $500  \nAmount: n. n = to the size of the mech that is being used. n = 1 is no mech.  \nDamage: 1D20 in a 5m radius.  \nRange: 200m  \nRequirements: Mech Workbench.  \n\n---\n\n\nGrapple hook Cannon**: A grappling hook that can only be equipped on basic mechs. Allows the mech to traverse up walls. Can also be used to drag enemies to you.  \nCost: $500  \nDamage: 1D4  \nRange: 100m  \nEffects: Allows mech to move up walls and buildings.  \nRequirements: Mech Workbench.[br]â€Œ  \n\n---\n\n\n**Armor Mod**: A upgrade to a mechsuit that takes away 1 weapon slot, but increases the armor of a mech by 2  \nCost: $100  \nRequirement: Mech workbench.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Mech Transformation Mod:** For 1 weapon slot you can make a mech have the ability to turn into a car.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nEffect: The mech can now turn into a car.\n\nRequirement: Mech Workbench\n\n---\n\n\n**Mech Bay:**Â A upgrade that can be made to any building that a car can enter or leave. Allows for the construction of bigger mechs and better weapons.  \nCost: $10000  \nRequirement: None\n\n---\n\n\n**Novice Mechsuit**: A mechsuit that seat 1 person. The size of a car. This mechsuit is built for more than just support and it shows.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nHP: 100\n\nMovespeed: 10m per turn\n\nArmor: 3\n\nWeapon slots: 3\n\nEffects: Increases strength to 15.\n\nRequirements: Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Laser Cannon**: A Massive laser cannon that has unlimited range.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nRange: Vision\n\nDamage: 1D10\n\nEffects: Double damage to unarmored targets.\n\nRequirements: Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Drill**: A Drill that can be used by mechs. Allows for the construction of underground complexes. Can be used as a improvised mellee weapon.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nRange: Touch\n\nDamage: nD10 damage. n= the level of mech being used. n = 1 is no mech.\n\nEffects: Allows for the digging of tunnels and underground chambers.\n\nRequirements: Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Trophy System**: A small laser system that destroys up to 3 physical ranged attacks every turn. Takes up 1 weapon slot.\n\nCost: $1000\n\nRange: 100m\n\nDamage: None\n\nEffects: Can destroy up to 3 physical ranged attacks per turn.\n\nRequirements: Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\n**Cargo Bay Mod**: A system that allows the mech to carry another person or something of similar size. Takes up 1 weapon slot.\n\nCost: $100\n\nEffect: Allows a Mech to carry something inside of it.\n\nRequirement: Mech Bay; Mech must be bigger than basic.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\nLv3\n---\n****\n**Mechs for dummies:**Â A manual that after being used allows for another person to use the mechs.  \nCost: $100  \nEffect: allows 1 person to be able to use mechs.  \nRequirement: None\n****\nFlight Mod: A mod that allows your mechs to fly.  \nCost: $ 1000  \nEffect: Allows any mech to have vertical movement\n\nRequirement: Mech Bay\n\n---\nâ€Œ\n\n\nMassive Mech Bay: A Building that needs to be built underground or in a big warehouse. It allows for the production of the biggest mechs and Strongest weapons.\n\nCost: $100000\n\nRequirement: None\n\n---\n\n\nAdvanced Mech: A massive 1 person mech. As big as a small building.\n\nCost: $100000\n\nHP: 1000\n\nMovespeed: 20m per turn.\n\nArmor: 10\n\nWeapon Slots: 5\n\nEffects: Increases your strength to 50\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nMIRV Missle launcher: A massive cluster bomb launcher that saturates a massive area with explosions.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nRange: 1km\n\nDamage: Hits every target within 250m radius of targeted area for 1D10 damage.\n\nRequirement: Massive Mech Bay.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nGatling Gun: A gun that shoots bullets at a ridiculous speed.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nRange: 200m\n\nDamage: 2nD4 n = to your mech level. n = 1 is no mech.\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nMech Dropship: A aircraft that can carry up to 10 basic mechsuits.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nMovespeed: 100m per turn\n\nHP: 150\n\nArmor: None\n\nWeapon slot: 1\n\nEffect: Can carry up to 10 basic mechsuits.\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nThermite Cannon: A gun that fires thermite that deals damage per turn.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nDamage: 1D8 per turn for 10 turns.\n\nRange: 200m\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nPotable Shield Projector: A force field projector that can be used for area denial by deploying walls.\n\nCost: $10000\n\nHP:20\n\nEffect: Allows the mech to project up to 3 walls with 20 hp each.\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nAi Mod: Allows a mech to control itself\n\nCost: $10000\n\nEffect: The Player can control any mech with this mod from another mech.\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nChest Mounted Mass Driver: A massive Railgun built into the chest of a mech.\n\nCost: $100000\n\nRange: Vision\n\nDamage: 1D100\n\nEffect: Can only be fired once a day.\n\nRequirements: Massive Mech Bay\n\n---\n\n\nLv4\n---\n\n\nOnly one of the following can be built.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nMech Titan: A Massive Mech the size of a skyscraper.\n\nCost: $1000000\n\nMovespeed: 50m per turn\n\nHP: 1000\n\nArmor: 20\n\nWeapon Slots: 10\n\nEffect: This Mech has to be built underground. When it emerges it destroys anything above it.\n\nRequirement: Built underground, Only one can exist.[br]â€Œ\n\n---\n\n\nMechanical Mecha Workshop: A entire workshop on legs. Counts as a Massive Mech Bay, Mech Bay and Mech Workbench.\n\nCost: $1000000\n\nMovespeed: 50m per turn.\n\nHP: 1000\n\nArmor: 20\n\nWeapon slot: 2\n\nEffect: This mech can carry any amount of other mechs and rapidly deploy them.\n\nRequirement: Must be built underground."},{"name":"Modular Items Techie","path":"Techie/Modular Items Techie.md","content":"Only you can use these items unless specified otherwise.\n- The player chooses **up to 3 modules** from this list.\n- They glue them together with a base chassis (free).\n- The final weapon gains **all ranges, damages, and effects** from every attached module.\n- If two modules give different ranges, it uses the **longest**.\n- If two modules give different damage dice, all dice apply.\n- If the weapon has both melee and ranged modules, it becomes **hybrid**.\n\n# Lv1\n\nLong Barrel: A extended long barrel to increase accuracy.\nCost: $100\nRange: 30m\nDamage: 1d4\nEffect: +2 to hit with ranged attacks\n\n---\nShort Barrel: A small barrel that helps with quick draw.\nCost: $100\nRange: 10m\nDamage: 1d6\nEffect: You can switch to this weapon as a free action \n\n---\nSplit Shot: A mod that splits bullets into a scatter effect.\nCost: $100\nDamage: 1d4\nEffect: Your attacks are split randomly across all the enemies in a cone.\n\n---\nStabilizer Grip: A gyroscope built into the handle of the weapon.\nCost: $100\nEffect: Consecutive attacks against the same enemy give +1 to hit.\n\n---\nShock Battery: A battery that discharges to stun the enemy\nCost: $100\nRange: Melee\nEffect: Once per turn. You stun an enemy on hit with a dc 6 durability save\n"},{"name":"Self Augment Techie","path":"Techie/Self Augment Techie.md","content":null},{"name":"Water Techie","path":"Techie/Water Techie.md","content":"\nOnly this player can use the supertech unless specified otherwise.\n\n\n# Lv1\n\nIgnition Gloves: A pair of fire proof gloves with a lighter built in.\nCost: $10\nEffects: Can ignite materials with touch. Reduces taken fire damage by 1.\nRequirements: None\n\n\n---\nFirestarter Paste: A thick paste made of flammable materials that burn for a long time.\nCost: $10\nEffects: Burns for 10 turns doing 1 damage per turn. Waterproof.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nFlashfuel Bottle: A small capsule filled with a volatile liquid.\nCost: $50\nEffects: Creates a 5m radius blast of light and fire. Deals 1d4 damage. Targets must make a reflex check of 5 or be blinded for 1 turn.\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nBasic Pyrotechnics Bench: A metal bench with ignition chambers, pressurized tanks, and controlled flame nozzles.\nCost: $100\nRequirements: None\n\n---\nIncendiary Gel: A sticky gel that burns brightly\nCost: $100\nEffects: Does 1d6 damage when thrown. Burns for 3 turns doing 1d4 damage a turn. Waterproof\nRequirements: Basic Pyrotechnics Bench\n\n---\nFlame Nozzle: A weak flamethrower that can launch your chemicals further.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Increases the effective range of your chemicals to 20m.\nRequirements: Basic Pyrotechnics Bench\n\n---\nFlame Suit: A insulated suit filled with fireproof materials.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Reduces taken fire damage by 4.\n\n---\nThermite Bomb: A large bundle of vials and packages with wires coming out of it.\nCost: $1000\nEffect: Causes an 10m explosion that coats everything in range with thermite. Coated enemies take 1d10 fire damage per turn for 10 turns."}];